headline: 1 Major Risk in Buying Costco Stock Right Now
summary: Costco Wholesale (NASDAQ: COST) has become a phenomenon.  Its differentiated warehouse retail model is incredibly reliable, and Costco consistently enjoys strong growth.  If you're considering buying Costco stock today, there's one major risk you need to know about as well.

headline: This Stock Is Up 106,400% Since Its IPO: Here's Why It Might Split in 2025.
summary: It is counterintuitive since it has nothing to do with the underlying business performance, but a stock split generates an average return of 25% to 30% in the following year, which usually beats the S&P 500 returns.  Here's why Costco stock might be headed for a split in 2025 and whether the 100,000%+ returner since its initial public offering (IPO) is a buy for investors today.  Costco's share price is closing in on $1,000, which has been a threshold when some companies have decided to split their shares.
